title <size:18>Customer Issue Resolution System (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Customer raises a billing issue. System auto-categorizes, assigns to agent via routing, agent resolves, customer rates resolution."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE
' ====================================================================
class IssueResolutionService <<Facade>> {
    - issues : Map<String, Issue>
    - agentPool : AgentPool
    - routingEngine : RoutingEngine
    - notificationService : NotificationService
    - escalationService : EscalationService
    - slaManager : SLAManager
    --
    + raiseIssue(customer, type, description) : Issue
    + resolveIssue(issueId, resolution) : void
    + escalateIssue(issueId) : void
    + reopenIssue(issueId, reason) : void
    + addComment(issueId, author, text) : void
    + getIssue(issueId) : Issue
    + getIssuesByCustomer(customerId) : List<Issue>
    + getAgentWorkload() : Map<String, Integer>
}

note top of IssueResolutionService #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "Customer calls support or raises a ticket.
    IssueResolutionService is the **Facade**
    — single API for raising issues, routing
    to agents, tracking status, escalation,
    and resolution. Hides all internal wiring."
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: CUSTOMER + AGENT MODELS
' ====================================================================
class Customer {
    - customerId : String
    - name : String
    - email : String
    - phone : String
    - tier : CustomerTier
    - issueHistory : List<Issue>
    --
    + getTier() : CustomerTier
    + getOpenIssueCount() : int
}

enum CustomerTier {
    REGULAR
    PREMIUM
    VIP
    ENTERPRISE
}

class Agent {
    - agentId : String
    - name : String
    - email : String
    - department : Department
    - skills : Set<IssueCategory>
    - status : AgentStatus
    - currentLoad : int
    - maxLoad : int
    - rating : double
    --
    + isAvailable() : boolean
    + canHandle(category) : boolean
    + assign() : void
    + release() : void
}

enum AgentStatus {
    AVAILABLE
    BUSY
    ON_BREAK
    OFFLINE
}

enum Department {
    BILLING
    TECHNICAL
    ACCOUNT
    SHIPPING
    GENERAL
}

class AgentPool {
    - agents : Map<String, Agent>
    - departmentIndex : Map<Department, List<Agent>>
    --
    + getAvailableAgents(dept) : List<Agent>
    + getAvailableAgents(dept, skill) : List<Agent>
    + getAgentLoad() : Map<String, Integer>
    + registerAgent(agent) : void
}

note top of Agent #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - Who is involved?**
    "**Customer** has a tier (REGULAR to VIP)
    — tier affects SLA and routing priority.
    **Agent** has department, skills (can handle
    BILLING, TECHNICAL, etc.), status, and
    current workload. **AgentPool** indexes
    agents by department for fast lookup."
end note

Customer --> CustomerTier
Agent --> AgentStatus
Agent --> Department
Agent --> IssueCategory : skilled in >
AgentPool o--> Agent : manages >
IssueResolutionService --> AgentPool
IssueResolutionService --> Customer : serves >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: ISSUE MODEL — Central Domain Object
' ====================================================================
class Issue {
    - issueId : String
    - customer : Customer
    - category : IssueCategory
    - priority : IssuePriority
    - description : String
    - assignedAgent : Agent
    - currentState : IssueState
    - status : IssueStatus
    - comments : List<Comment>
    - resolution : Resolution
    - createdAt : LocalDateTime
    - resolvedAt : LocalDateTime
    - slaDeadline : LocalDateTime
    - escalationLevel : int
    - observers : List<IssueObserver>
    --
    + assign(agent) : void
    + resolve(resolution) : void
    + escalate() : void
    + reopen(reason) : void
    + close() : void
    + addComment(comment) : void
    + registerObserver(obs) : void
    + notifyObservers(event) : void
    + isSLABreached() : boolean
}

enum IssueCategory {
    BILLING
    TECHNICAL
    ACCOUNT_ACCESS
    SHIPPING
    REFUND
    FEATURE_REQUEST
    COMPLAINT
}

enum IssuePriority {
    LOW
    MEDIUM
    HIGH
    CRITICAL
}

enum IssueStatus {
    OPEN
    ASSIGNED
    IN_PROGRESS
    WAITING_ON_CUSTOMER
    ESCALATED
    RESOLVED
    CLOSED
    REOPENED
}

class Comment {
    - commentId : String
    - author : String
    - text : String
    - timestamp : LocalDateTime
    - isInternal : boolean
}

class Resolution {
    - resolutionType : ResolutionType
    - description : String
    - resolvedBy : Agent
    - resolvedAt : LocalDateTime
    - customerSatisfied : boolean
}

enum ResolutionType {
    FIXED
    WORKAROUND
    DUPLICATE
    WONT_FIX
    REFUNDED
    ESCALATED_EXTERNALLY
}

note top of Issue #FFCDD2
    **STEP 3 - Issue is the central object.**
    "Has category, priority, assigned agent,
    state, SLA deadline, comments, and
    resolution. Uses **State Pattern**
    (lifecycle), **Observer** (notifications),
    and **Chain of Responsibility** (routing)."
end note

Issue --> IssueCategory
Issue --> IssuePriority
Issue --> IssueStatus
Issue --> Customer : raised by >
Issue --> Agent : assigned to >
Issue *-- Comment : has comments >
Issue --> Resolution : resolved with >
Resolution --> ResolutionType
Resolution --> Agent : by >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: ISSUE STATE — State Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface IssueState <<State>> {
    + assign(issue, agent) : void
    + startWork(issue) : void
    + waitOnCustomer(issue) : void
    + resolve(issue, resolution) : void
    + escalate(issue) : void
    + reopen(issue, reason) : void
    + close(issue) : void
}

class OpenState {
    + assign(issue, agent) : void
    + escalate(issue) : void
    + close(issue) : void
}

class AssignedState {
    + startWork(issue) : void
    + escalate(issue) : void
    + assign(issue, agent) : void
}

class InProgressState {
    + resolve(issue, resolution) : void
    + waitOnCustomer(issue) : void
    + escalate(issue) : void
}

class WaitingOnCustomerState {
    + startWork(issue) : void
    + close(issue) : void
    + escalate(issue) : void
}

class EscalatedState {
    + assign(issue, agent) : void
    + resolve(issue, resolution) : void
}

class ResolvedState {
    + reopen(issue, reason) : void
    + close(issue) : void
}

class ClosedState {
    + reopen(issue, reason) : void
}

note bottom of IssueState #FFCDD2
    **STEP 4 - Issue lifecycle.**
    "**State Pattern** — each state is a class.
    **Open**: just created, can assign/escalate.
    **Assigned**: agent assigned, can start work.
    **InProgress**: agent working, can resolve/wait/escalate.
    **WaitingOnCustomer**: need info from customer.
    **Escalated**: bumped to senior/manager.
    **Resolved**: fixed, customer can reopen.
    **Closed**: terminal (can still reopen)."

    Open -> Assigned -> InProgress -> Resolved -> Closed
    InProgress -> WaitingOnCustomer -> InProgress
    Any -> Escalated -> Assigned (reassigned)
    Resolved/Closed -> Open (reopened)
    **Pattern: State | SRP, OCP**
end note

IssueState <|.. OpenState
IssueState <|.. AssignedState
IssueState <|.. InProgressState
IssueState <|.. WaitingOnCustomerState
IssueState <|.. EscalatedState
IssueState <|.. ResolvedState
IssueState <|.. ClosedState
Issue --> IssueState : delegates >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: ROUTING — Chain of Responsibility
' ====================================================================
abstract class RoutingHandler <<Handler>> {
    # nextHandler : RoutingHandler
    --
    + setNext(handler) : RoutingHandler
    + {abstract} handle(issue) : Agent
}

class CategoryRoutingHandler {
    --
    + handle(issue) : Agent
}

class PriorityRoutingHandler {
    --
    + handle(issue) : Agent
}

class CustomerTierRoutingHandler {
    --
    + handle(issue) : Agent
}

class LoadBalancingHandler {
    --
    + handle(issue) : Agent
}

class RoutingEngine {
    - handlerChain : RoutingHandler
    --
    + route(issue) : Agent
    + buildChain() : void
}

note bottom of RoutingHandler #FFE0B2
    **STEP 5 - Who handles this issue? (KEY STEP)**
    "Issue raised. Which agent gets it?
    **Chain of Responsibility Pattern**:"

    "1. **CategoryHandler**: route BILLING to
       Billing dept, TECHNICAL to Tech dept.
    2. **PriorityHandler**: CRITICAL goes to
       senior agents only.
    3. **CustomerTierHandler**: VIP/Enterprise
       get dedicated agents.
    4. **LoadBalancingHandler**: among eligible
       agents, pick the least loaded."

    "Each handler refines the selection or
    passes to next. Add SkillBasedHandler?
    Insert in chain. Nothing else changes."
    **Pattern: Chain of Responsibility | OCP, SRP**
end note

RoutingHandler <|-- CategoryRoutingHandler
RoutingHandler <|-- PriorityRoutingHandler
RoutingHandler <|-- CustomerTierRoutingHandler
RoutingHandler <|-- LoadBalancingHandler
RoutingHandler o--> RoutingHandler : next >
RoutingEngine --> RoutingHandler : uses chain >
IssueResolutionService --> RoutingEngine


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: SLA MANAGEMENT — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
class SLAManager {
    - slaPolicy : SLAPolicy
    --
    + calculateDeadline(issue) : LocalDateTime
    + isSLABreached(issue) : boolean
    + getTimeRemaining(issue) : long
    + checkAllSLAs() : List<Issue>
}

interface SLAPolicy <<Strategy>> {
    + getResponseTimeHours(priority, tier) : int
    + getResolutionTimeHours(priority, tier) : int
}

class StandardSLAPolicy {
    --
    + getResponseTimeHours(priority, tier) : int
    + getResolutionTimeHours(priority, tier) : int
}

class PremiumSLAPolicy {
    --
    + getResponseTimeHours(priority, tier) : int
    + getResolutionTimeHours(priority, tier) : int
}

class EnterpriseSLAPolicy {
    --
    + getResponseTimeHours(priority, tier) : int
    + getResolutionTimeHours(priority, tier) : int
}

note bottom of SLAPolicy #D1C4E9
    **STEP 6 - SLA enforcement.**
    "Each issue has an SLA deadline based
    on priority + customer tier.
    **Strategy Pattern** — SLA rules are pluggable."

    "**Standard**: CRITICAL=4hr, HIGH=24hr.
    **Premium**: CRITICAL=1hr, HIGH=4hr.
    **Enterprise**: CRITICAL=30min, custom terms."

    "SLAManager.checkAllSLAs() finds breached
    issues and triggers auto-escalation."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

SLAPolicy <|.. StandardSLAPolicy
SLAPolicy <|.. PremiumSLAPolicy
SLAPolicy <|.. EnterpriseSLAPolicy
SLAManager --> SLAPolicy : delegates >
IssueResolutionService --> SLAManager


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: ESCALATION — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
class EscalationService {
    - escalationStrategy : EscalationStrategy
    - slaManager : SLAManager
    --
    + escalate(issue) : void
    + autoEscalateBreachedSLAs() : void
}

interface EscalationStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + getNextLevel(issue) : EscalationTarget
}

class HierarchicalEscalation {
    --
    + getNextLevel(issue) : EscalationTarget
}

class DepartmentHeadEscalation {
    --
    + getNextLevel(issue) : EscalationTarget
}

class ExternalEscalation {
    --
    + getNextLevel(issue) : EscalationTarget
}

class EscalationTarget {
    - agent : Agent
    - level : int
    - reason : String
}

note bottom of EscalationStrategy #FFCDD2
    **STEP 7 - Issue not resolved in time.**
    "SLA breached or customer unhappy.
    **Strategy Pattern** — escalation path
    is pluggable."

    "**Hierarchical**: agent -> team lead -> manager.
    **DepartmentHead**: skip to dept head directly.
    **External**: route to external vendor/partner."

    "EscalationService.autoEscalateBreachedSLAs()
    runs periodically, finds overdue issues,
    escalates automatically."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, SRP**
end note

EscalationStrategy <|.. HierarchicalEscalation
EscalationStrategy <|.. DepartmentHeadEscalation
EscalationStrategy <|.. ExternalEscalation
EscalationStrategy --> EscalationTarget
EscalationService --> EscalationStrategy : delegates >
EscalationService --> SLAManager : checks >
IssueResolutionService --> EscalationService


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: OBSERVER — Notifications + Tracking
' ====================================================================
interface IssueObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onIssueEvent(issue, event) : void
}

class CustomerNotifyObserver {
    + onIssueEvent(issue, event) : void
}

class AgentNotifyObserver {
    + onIssueEvent(issue, event) : void
}

class SLAWatchdogObserver {
    - slaManager : SLAManager
    --
    + onIssueEvent(issue, event) : void
}

class DashboardObserver {
    + onIssueEvent(issue, event) : void
}

class AuditTrailObserver {
    + onIssueEvent(issue, event) : void
}

note bottom of IssueObserver #B2EBF2
    **STEP 8 - Everyone stays informed.**
    "On every state change, Issue calls
    notifyObservers(). **Observer Pattern**:"

    "**CustomerObserver**: 'Your issue is assigned.'
    **AgentObserver**: 'New issue assigned to you.'
    **SLAWatchdog**: starts/checks SLA timer.
    **DashboardObserver**: updates live metrics
    (open issues, avg resolution time).
    **AuditTrailObserver**: logs for compliance."
    **Pattern: Observer | OCP, SRP**
end note

IssueObserver <|.. CustomerNotifyObserver
IssueObserver <|.. AgentNotifyObserver
IssueObserver <|.. SLAWatchdogObserver
IssueObserver <|.. DashboardObserver
IssueObserver <|.. AuditTrailObserver
Issue --> IssueObserver : notifies >
SLAWatchdogObserver --> SLAManager : checks >

class NotificationService {
    - strategies : List<NotificationStrategy>
    --
    + notify(recipient, message) : void
}

interface NotificationStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class EmailNotification {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class SMSNotification {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class InAppNotification {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

NotificationStrategy <|.. EmailNotification
NotificationStrategy <|.. SMSNotification
NotificationStrategy <|.. InAppNotification
NotificationService --> NotificationStrategy
CustomerNotifyObserver --> NotificationService : uses >
AgentNotifyObserver --> NotificationService : uses >
IssueResolutionService --> NotificationService


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 9: CUSTOMER SATISFACTION
' ====================================================================
class FeedbackService {
    - feedbacks : Map<String, Feedback>
    --
    + submitFeedback(issueId, score, comment) : Feedback
    + getAgentRating(agentId) : double
    + getCSATScore(from, to) : double
}

class Feedback {
    - feedbackId : String
    - issueId : String
    - customerId : String
    - score : int
    - comment : String
    - submittedAt : LocalDateTime
}

note bottom of FeedbackService #C8E6C9
    **STEP 9 - Close the loop.**
    "After resolution, customer rates 1-5
    and optionally comments. FeedbackService
    computes CSAT score and individual
    agent ratings. Low score can trigger
    auto-reopen. Feeds into agent performance."
end note

FeedbackService --> Feedback : manages >
Feedback --> Issue
Feedback --> Customer
IssueResolutionService --> FeedbackService


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "Customer raises billing issue -> auto-categorized ->
    **Chain of Responsibility** routes: category -> priority -> tier ->
    load balance -> agent assigned. Issue moves through states (**State
    Pattern**): Open -> Assigned -> InProgress -> Resolved -> Closed.
    SLA tracked per customer tier (**SLA Strategy**). SLA breached?
    Auto-escalated (**Escalation Strategy**). Customer, agent, dashboard,
    audit all notified (**Observer**). Customer rates resolution.
    6 patterns: **Facade, Chain of Responsibility, State, Strategy (x3), Observer**."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | Customer calls IssueResolutionService.raiseIssue() | Facade | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | Customer (with tier), Agent (with skills/dept/load), AgentPool | -- | SRP |
    | 3 | Issue: category, priority, SLA deadline, comments, resolution | -- | SRP |
    | 4 | Open -> Assigned -> InProgress -> Resolved -> Closed (+ Escalated, Reopened) | State | SRP, OCP |
    | 5 | Route: category -> priority -> tier -> least loaded agent | Chain of Responsibility | OCP, SRP |
    | 6 | SLA deadline by priority + tier (Standard/Premium/Enterprise) | Strategy | OCP, DIP |
    | 7 | Escalate: hierarchical / dept head / external | Strategy | OCP, SRP |
    | 8 | Customer, agent, SLA watchdog, dashboard, audit notified | Observer + Strategy | OCP, SRP |
    | 9 | Customer rates resolution, CSAT score computed | -- | SRP |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Route + Assign** = Steps 2,5 | **Lifecycle** = Step 4 | **SLA + Escalate** = Steps 6-7 | **Notify + Rate** = Steps 8-9 |
endlegend

@enduml
